Integer.Description:
Arguments for DFU command (firmware update of the MDlink and MDTile modules). Should coincide with arguments of the feature AccessCodeDFU (for protective puposes). D31 1 - block DFU-access through other channels D[27:24] Code of operation 8 Chip erasing 9 Sectors erasing D[23:8] high-order bits of the initial sector D[7:0] number of sectors D[7:0] protective code 1 Reading Capacity ID 2 Reading Silicon ID 3 Reading Status
4 Reconfigurator parameters reading, D[30:28] parameter number. 5 Reconfigurator parameters writing, D[30:28] - parameter number, D[23:0] - parameter 6 Reconfiguration start
R (if one uses getFeature) Status to be returned: D31 - Busy, D25 - Illegal Erase, D24 - Illegal Write D[23:16] - CapID, D[15:8] - SilID, D[7:0] - Status

Integer.Name: SyncConfiguration
Integer.ToolTip: Configuring of the sync-signals
Integer.Description:
Triggering In/Out configuration
Reserved [3:0]
External Input selection: [5:4] 0 - SYNC_IN ("SYNC" optocoupler input) 1 - SYNC_CTS (RS232 input) 2 - SyncPhoto (AED) 3 TEST (Do not use)
Reserved [7:6]
SYNC_IN polarity [8] 0 active state when current is Off (no Input) 1 - active state when current is On
SYNC_CTS polarity [9] 0 - active state when VIN is Negative, 1 - active state when VIN is Positive
Reserved [10]
External Output selection: [13:12] 0 - SYNC_OUT (optocoupler output) 1 - SYNC_RTS (RS-232 output) 2 - SYNC_TXD (RS-232 output) 3 No output signal
Output PullUp (+5V, 1k) at the SYNC_OUT: [15] 1 pull-up is enabled, 0 pull-up is disabled
SYNC_OUT polarity: [16] 0 the output switch is ON in active state 1 - the output switch is OFF in active state
SYNC_RTS polarity [17] 0 VOUT is Negative, 1 VOUT is Positive

Category.Description: Category that contains acquisition configuration features.

Integer.Name: GrbCh0TrigCfgFrameToSkip
Integer.ToolTip: Controls the number of frames to skip between successively acquired frames.
Integer.Description: Controls the number of frames to skip between successively acquired frames. A value of 0 sends all frames. A value of 1 sends one frame and discards one. A value of 2 sends one frame and discards two, etc.

Enumeration.Name: GrbCh0TrigCfgContinuousPipeCount
Enumeration.ToolTip: Controls the number of GigE Vision blocks (frames) that can be in the acquisition and transfer pipe.
Enumeration.Description: Controls the number of GigE Vision blocks (frames) that can be in the acquisition and transfer pipe. A frame is considered to be in the pipe from the moment it starts until its last packet is transmitted on the Ethernet link. When the specified number of frames is reached, the IP engine ignores any new frames from the camera head until the number of frames in the pipe decreases. In continuous pipe count or recording acquisition modes, the limit is set by the amount of onboard memory available in the IP engine, rather than the number of frames in the pipe. The IP engine acquires frames from the camera until the memory is filled up to the water-level setting (GrbCh0AcqCfgMemoryWaterLevel).

Boolean.Name: GrbCh0TrigCfgAutomaticInternalRetrigger
Boolean.ToolTip: Determines whether the IP engine is automatically retrigged when FVAL stays high and the IP engine has completed the current acquisition.
Boolean.Description: Determines whether the IP engine is automatically retrigged when FVAL stays high and the IP engine has completed the current acquisition. When this feature is disabled, the IP engine waits for the next rising edge of FVAL to acquire another image.

Boolean.Name: GrbCh0TrigCfgPLCTriggerable
Boolean.ToolTip: Determines whether the PLC Q14 output is used to trigger the acquisition of a frame.
Boolean.Description: Determines whether the PLC Q14 output is used to trigger the acquisition of a frame. When enabled, this is the IP engine that is triggered, not the camera head.
